@model ProjectQ.Models.HotPlaceExplorer

It looks like you're in <span class="badge badge-warning">@Model.BasePlace.BaseTown</span> where it's <span class="badge badge-warning">@Model.BasePlace.BaseTemp.ToString()ºC</span>
<br /><br />
@if (Model.BasePlace.BaseTemp == Model.HottestPlace.HotTemp)
{
    <span> There nowhere hotter nearby, maybe put on a sweater.</span>
}
else
{
    <span>We've chased the sun and the hottest place we've found is <span class="badge badge-warning">@Model.HottestPlace.HotTown </span> which is a toasty <span class="badge badge-warning">@(Model.HottestPlace.HotTemp)ºC</span> </span>
    <br /><br />
    <span>If you hopped in the car now you could be <span class="badge badge-warning">@(Model.DegreesHotter)ºC</span> hotter in <span class="badge badge-warning">@Model.RouteToHottest.TimeAsText </span> </span>
    <br /><br />
    <span>If you don't want to get any colder along the way you can retrace our steps and go via these lovely places:</span>
    <br /><br />
    <table class="table">
        @foreach (var town in Model.SearchList)
        {
            <tr class="table-warning"><td>@town</td></tr>
        }
    </table>
}
